May be an image of text that says 'LESS IMPORTANT FOR A RELATIONSHIP To BE HEALTHY: -Sharing kissing selfies online MORE IMPORTANT FOR A RELATIONSHIP To BE HEALTHY: -Having the difficult conversations -Open communication -Building trust -Setting and respecting boundaries -Working together through traumas -Prioritizing Mental Health needs'.

node.text: Nothing wrong with a nice kissing selfie but it’s probably not going to be the foundation of a healthy relationship. Friendly reminder to make sure you are spending the needed time + energy on the actual relationship, and not just the aesthetic of the relationship online 🗣🔥

May be an image of text that says 'Social Anxiety WHAT IT FEELS LIKE Trembling Worrying for days before an event Upset stomach WHATI IT IKE Worrying intensely about social situations Fear of embarrassment Rapid heat rate Avoiding social situations Needing alcohol for social situations @letstalk.mentalhealth Shaky voice'.

node.text:
I wanted to provide a really clear diagram of what social anxiety can feel like as many of us experience it to some extent

Please comment what resonates most with you. 

For me, it’s shaky voice and leaving early. One remedy I use to calm my voice is to humm when I feel my social anxiety kicking it. It helps relax the voice and people have used humming for centuries to calm down. 

Please share any tips you have 🗣🔥

node.text:
When was the last time you cried?

Crying is a common human action, and it can be triggered by many different emotions. Crying can be a natural release for us, and has many benefits 

Source: medicalnewstoday & healthline

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lets Talk Mental Health in San Diego, California with @letstalk.mentalhealth. May be an image of text that says 'Things Your Partner is NOT Responsible For: Your Happiness Reading Your Mind Your Feelings Things Your Patner is Responsible For: Their Own Happiness Communicating Their Feelings @letstalk.mentalhealth'.

node.text:
We get into trouble when we start relying on our partners to be responsible for any of the above. A consistently supportive partner is one who is also able to manage their own emotions and feelings. 

What else do you feel a partner is / is not responsible for? 🗣🔥

This doesn’t apply to abusive partners who mess with your feelings. I’ll also add that we are all responsible for how we treat others and what types of behaviors we choose to tolerate from others in our lives ❤️❤️❤️
